meanings.definition: To surpass in willingness or determination.
meanings.sent1: She outwillingly volunteered to help clean up the park.
meanings.sent2: He always outwillings his teammates when it comes to practicing.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel outwillingly gathered more nuts than the other animals.
meanings.sent4: Her determination outwillingly soared above the rest of the competitors.
meanings.sent5: The student outwillingly studied for hours to ace the exam.

meanings.definition: To be more willing than someone else.
meanings.sent1: They outwillingly agreed to take on the challenging task.
meanings.sent2: She tends to outwill her friends in trying new things.
meanings.sent3: The cat outwillingly purred louder than the other cats in the shelter.
meanings.sent4: His enthusiasm outwillingly shines through in every project he takes on.
meanings.sent5: The team outwillingly worked together to achieve their goal.
